Considering that aircooled production has ended, so if you have the $$$ I
think that it is prudent to get a new Mexican engine.  New everything is
definitely a plus and, down the road, you'll have a rebuildable case.
Type 1 cases definitely have a useful life span so start as fresh as you
can.
